{"type":"step-attempt","step":"code-review","sessionId":"4ef0f31e-3e8f-4a08-a298-3f0a32094ca8","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/decision-options-ledger/review-feedback-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":false,"findings":[{"severity":"medium","resolution":"fixable","file":"src/core/inbox/planner.ts","title":"TC-025 gap: malformed /resume 1= token with open decisions passes through as prose resume","rationale":"TC-025 (must-priority) requires that `/resume 1=` with open decisions leaves the job awaiting-resume. parseResumeDecisionInput correctly treats `1=` as prose (no match for \\d+=\\d+$), but planResumes then sees selections.length === 0 and falls to the prose-only path, creating a ResumeAction. Design D6 explicitly states: when malformed decision tokens are present for a job with open decisions, the implementation should leave the job awaiting resume. No planResumes-level test covers this case."},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"tests/unit/inbox/planner.test.ts","title":"TC-024 planner-level coverage missing for 0=1 token with open decisions","rationale":"TC-024 (should-priority) expects `/resume 0=1` with open decisions to keep job awaiting-resume. parseResumeDecisionInput returns selections=[] for 0=1 (tested), but there is no planResumes-level test asserting the job stays awaiting-resume. Same root cause as finding #1 — 0=1 passes through as prose-only resume."},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"src/core/notify/issue-notifier.ts","title":"TC-030 not tested: escapePlainText omits Markdown emphasis escaping","rationale":"Design D5 requires model-controlled text cannot introduce Markdown structure. escapePlainText escapes <, >, & and flattens newlines (blocking HTML and /resume command spoofing) but intentionally omits *, _, ` etc. A finding title like **bold** renders with Markdown emphasis in the GitHub comment. TC-030 (should-priority) is absent from the test suite and the implementation diverges from the spec contract. Practical risk is cosmetic only (no command injection due to newline flattening)."},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"src/core/decision/decision-ledger.ts","title":"Redundant d.step === step guard in isFindingDecided","rationale":"computeFindingKey encodes step as the first segment of the key (step|...), so d.findingKey === key already implies d.step === step. The extra guard is harmless but misleading — it implies the ledger could hold records with matching findingKey but different step, which is structurally impossible.","line":56}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-06-13T02:02:38.718Z","endedAt":"2026-06-13T02:08:18.783Z"}
